Vice Principal Needed for Abu Dhabi International School
Work at a beautiful new International Private School in the city of Al-Ain, UAE. Al Ain, also known as the Garden City due to its greenery, is the second largest city in the Emirate of Abu Dhabi and the fourth largest city in the United Arab Emirates.We are looking for certified and experienced assistant principals to work at a private international school in Al-Ain, UAE. Start Date: September 1, 2014Basic Position RequirementsPlease have a look at the basic requirements for our positions to see if you qualify for our positions.Native English speakers from Canada and the United States onlyUniversity Degree in Education/Primary Education/Early Childhood Education5 years of formal teaching experience with young learners2 years of formal experience working as a vice principal or principalPlease note that if you do not meet the above-mentioned requirements, we cannot consider you for this position. Salary and Benefits PackageYour teaching package includes:Private furnished accommodation with paid water and electricity billsAnnual round trip ticketsWork transportation is free of chargeMedical and health insurance providedA non-taxable monthly salary starting at USD$3,800+. Your salary package will be determined by your experience and qualifications.If you're interested in this incredible opportunity, please don't delay. We have a limited number of positions on offer, and we expect that they will go quickly!
